******
[1]
Date: 28 Jun 2012
Source: RUI Novosti [edited]
http://www.ria.ru/society/20120628/687171854.html


A total of 6 people, including a pregnant woman, have been hospitalized in Dagestan with suspected cutaneous anthrax, according to Ruslan Ozdemir, head of the Dagestan state veterinary control management Rosselkhoznadzor.

"According to preliminary data, on 15 Jun 2012 a sick animal [presumably a bovine - Mod.MHJ] was slaughtered in the Ahvahskom region of Dagestan and its meat sold in a local market, which resulted in the illness of the 6 sick people. 5 patients are in a district hospital and the pregnant woman was taken to the infectious diseases hospital in Makhachkala," a spokesman said.

Currently, a Rosselkhoznadzor officer in conjunction with the prosecutor's office is investigating this outbreak.

