[Reports of anthrax in Dagestan are spotty at best. OIE reported a single bovine case and 3 ovine/caprine outbreaks in 2005, one ovine/caprine case in 2006, and 2 outbreaks in 2010 (one involving a cow and the other a sheep), which is typical of reports culled from diagnostic laboratory log books, which reflect submissions but not the actual events. It did not report the 2011 events commented upon by the Caucasian Know. The 2010 sheep outbreak resulted in 2 people being infected. I think we can assume that livestock anthrax is commoner in the Republic of Dagestan than the records demonstrate.

Dagestan is on the west bank of the Caspian Sea; see:
http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/commonwealth/caucasus_region_1994.jpg. Gimry is due west of Makhachkala at:
http://www.fallingrain.com/world/RS/17/Gimry.html.
- Mod.MHJ]
